> protocol removal will be done in the protocol repository
> Sorry, I missed this.

@kezhenxu94, what do you mean about `will be`? Are you going to provide another pull request to update the submodule? I prefer it should be done on this one only, to make sure the removal is completed. FYI @JaredTan95

For the rules you want to set, I am good with them. 

> And I suggest the works could be done right before our next release, after all(or most) pull requests have been merged, and the codebase is frozen, to avoid conflicts;

I think we may not need to wait for this. It is hard to tell the time, whenever this is ready, please submit the pull request. As we check all these in the CI process, other PRs will be required to change.

> You need to check why Jeager missed the service name

@wu-sheng  thanks for quick reply! if Jaeger missed the service name, then how could it show that in its UI?

My guess is skywalking and Jaeger may be checking different field for "service name"?
